(26, 'Armitage Tuto', '<p id=\"1d4e\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo fr lp b lq lr ls lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">In case it isnt preinstalled, run the following commands on your terminal -</p>\r\n<pre class=\"mo mp mq mr ms nu nv nw nx ax ny bj\"><span id=\"f2d3\" class=\"nz oa fr nv b hl ob oc l od oe\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">deb <a class=\"af of\" href=\"http://http.kali.org/kali\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://http.kali.org/kali</a> kali main non-free contrib</span><span id=\"f7f3\" class=\"nz oa fr nv b hl og oc l od oe\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">deb-src <a class=\"af of\" href=\"http://http.kali.org/kali\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://http.kali.org/kali</a> kali main non-free contrib</span><span id=\"61ba\" class=\"nz oa fr nv b hl og oc l od oe\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">apt-get update</span><span id=\"90c1\" class=\"nz oa fr nv b hl og oc l od oe\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">apt-get install armitage</span></pre>\r\n<p id=\"efe8\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo fr lp b lq lr ls lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Since, this tool uses<strong class=\"lp fs\"> Metasploit as a backend</strong>, it is mandatory that it is installed on your attacking machine/system.</p>\r\n<p id=\"aef1\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo fr lp b lq lr ls lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">With all that done, Let&rsquo;s begin with the main process.</p>\r\n<h1 id=\"e915\" class=\"oh oa fr be oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq or os ot ou ov ow ox oy oz pa pb pc pd bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Detection of System</h1>\r\n<p id=\"3327\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo fr lp b lq pe ls lt lu pf lw lx ly pg ma mb mc ph me mf mg pi mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Firstly, we shall check if our virtual machine is indeed active and vulnerable at the same time. To do this we run a <strong class=\"lp fs\">Quick Scan </strong>using <strong class=\"lp fs\">Zenmap</strong> (on our attacking Kali Device where we will be using Armitage).</p>\r\n<figure class=\"mo mp mq mr ms mt ml mm paragraph-image\">\r\n<div role=\"button\" class=\"nl nm ee nn bg no\" tabindex=\"0\">\r\n<div class=\"ml mm pj\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" type=\"image/webp\"><source data-testid=\"og\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*XJtZ1Zk6MsMllT5uKxqj8Q.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></picture></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"np nq nr ml mm ns nt be b bf z dw\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">NMap Scan of our Target Windows 7 System</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"5148\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo fr lp b lq lr ls lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">We are able to see that the system is available since we are able to list the open services with their details.</p>\r\n<h1 id=\"3664\" class=\"oh oa fr be oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq or os ot ou ov ow ox oy oz pa pb pc pd bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Starting up Armitage</h1>\r\n<p id=\"fb37\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo fr lp b lq pe ls lt lu pf lw lx ly pg ma mb mc ph me mf mg pi mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Before beginning Armitage itself, if you are on an older version of Kali Linux (2.x), we must run the following command -</p>\r\n<figure class=\"mo mp mq mr ms mt ml mm paragraph-image\">\r\n<div class=\"ml mm pk\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1204/format:webp/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 1204w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 602px\" type=\"image/webp\"><source data-testid=\"og\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1204/1*hd5_tEsGgDm8-nD0YyHKrA.png 1204w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 602px\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"np nq nr ml mm ns nt be b bf z dw\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Command &mdash; &ldquo;msfdb init&rdquo;</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<blockquote class=\"pl pm pn\">\r\n<p id=\"33df\" class=\"ln lo po lp b lq lr ls lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Note &mdash; In case you run Armitage before doing this, you are notified on what solutions you have in order to start Armitage correctly. It necessarily needs a database.yml file to run so a GUI popup comes on and you can execute the solutions by yourself.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p id=\"c2a9\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo fr lp b lq lr ls lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">After all that, we just need to boot up Armitage. To do that we need to run the tool as root using the following commands -</p>\r\n<pre class=\"language-php\"><code>service postgresql start\r\nsudo Armitage</code></pre>\r\n<p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo fr lp b lq lr ls lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk fk bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"></p>', 1, '665f90db14151.png', '2024-06-04 22:10:35'),
(28, 'Explain Schéma Active Directory', '<p>Le sch&eacute;ma Microsoft Active Directory contient des d&eacute;finitions formelles de chaque classe d&rsquo;objets qui peuvent &ecirc;tre cr&eacute;&eacute;es dans une for&ecirc;t Active Directory. Le sch&eacute;ma contient &eacute;galement des d&eacute;finitions formelles de chaque attribut qui peut exister dans un objet Active Directory. Cette section fournit la r&eacute;f&eacute;rence pour chaque objet de sch&eacute;ma et fournit une br&egrave;ve explication des attributs, classes et autres objets qui composent le sch&eacute;ma Active Directory.</p>\r\n<div class=\"alert is-info\">\r\n<p class=\"alert-title\"><span class=\"docon docon-status-error-outline\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span> Notes</p>\r\n<p>La documentation suivante contient les r&eacute;f&eacute;rences de programmation pour le sch&eacute;ma Active Directory. Si vous &ecirc;tes un utilisateur final qui tente de d&eacute;boguer une erreur d&rsquo;imprimante, essayez de rechercher sur le <a href=\"https://answers.microsoft.com\" data-linktype=\"external\">site de la communaut&eacute; Microsoft</a>. Si vous &ecirc;tes d&eacute;veloppeur &agrave; la recherche d&rsquo;une vue d&rsquo;ensemble du sch&eacute;ma Active Directory, consultez les rubriques Vue d&rsquo;ensemble <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/fr-fr/windows/desktop/AD/active-directory-schema\" data-linktype=\"absolute-path\">du sch&eacute;ma Active Directory</a> . Si vous recherchez des instructions de programmation pour la mise &agrave; jour ou la modification du sch&eacute;ma, pour plus d&rsquo;informations sur l&rsquo;extension et la personnalisation du sch&eacute;ma, consultez <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/fr-fr/windows/desktop/AD/extending-the-schema\" data-linktype=\"absolute-path\">Extension du sch&eacute;ma</a>, ainsi que de nombreuses rubriques des guides de programmation <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/fr-fr/windows/desktop/AD/active-directory-domain-services\" data-linktype=\"absolute-path\">des services d&rsquo;annuaire l&eacute;ger services de domaine Active Directory</a> et <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/fr-fr/previous-versions/windows/desktop/adam/active-directory-lightweight-directory-services\" data-linktype=\"absolute-path\">Active Directory</a>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Dans chacune des rubriques de r&eacute;f&eacute;rence, il existe une section pour chaque syst&egrave;me d&rsquo;exploitation auquel la rubrique s&rsquo;applique. Les syst&egrave;mes d&rsquo;exploitation suivants sont actuellement pris en charge.</p>\r\n<div class=\"buttons buttons-right margin-bottom-none margin-top-sm\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"buttons buttons-right margin-bottom-none margin-top-sm\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"has-inner-focus\">\r\n<table aria-label=\"Table 1\" class=\"table table-sm margin-top-none\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Plateforme</th>\r\n<th>Nom dans la rubrique</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Microsoft Windows Server&nbsp;2003</td>\r\n<td>Windows Server&nbsp;2003</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Mode d&rsquo;application Microsoft Active Directory (ADAM)</td>\r\n<td>ADAM</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Microsoft Windows Server&nbsp;2003&nbsp;R2</td>\r\n<td>Windows Server&nbsp;2003&nbsp;R2</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Microsoft Windows Server&nbsp;2008</td>\r\n<td>Microsoft Windows Server&nbsp;2008</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Microsoft Windows Server 2008 R2</td>\r\n<td>Microsoft Windows Server 2008 R2</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Microsoft Windows Server 2012</td>\r\n<td>Microsoft Windows Server 2012</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Si un syst&egrave;me d&rsquo;exploitation n&rsquo;est pas r&eacute;pertori&eacute; dans la rubrique, la rubrique n&rsquo;est pas prise en charge sur ce syst&egrave;me d&rsquo;exploitation. Par exemple, si une rubrique r&eacute;pertorie uniquement Windows Server 2003 et ADAM, la rubrique ne s&rsquo;applique pas &agrave; Windows Server 2003 R2.</p>\r\n<p>Les sections suivantes contiennent des informations d&eacute;taill&eacute;es sur les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de sch&eacute;ma Active Directory.</p>', 1, NULL, '2024-06-04 22:14:16'),
(29, 'How To Remove Docker Images', '<h3 id=\"introduction\"><a href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-remove-docker-images-containers-and-volumes#introduction\" onclick=\"navigator.clipboard.writeText(this.href);\">Introduction</a><a class=\"hash-anchor\" href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-remove-docker-images-containers-and-volumes#introduction\" aria-hidden=\"true\" onclick=\"navigator.clipboard.writeText(this.href);\"></a></h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.docker.com/\" rel=\"ugc nofollow\">Docker</a> makes it easy to wrap your applications and services in containers so you can run them anywhere. However, as you work with Docker, it&rsquo;s also easy to accumulate an excessive number of unused images, containers, and data volumes that clutter the output and consume disk space.</p>\r\n<p>Docker gives you all the tools you need to clean up your system from the command line. This cheat sheet-style guide provides a quick reference to commands that are useful for freeing disk space and keeping your system organized by removing unused Docker images, containers, and volumes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How to Use This Guide:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>This guide is in cheat sheet format with self-contained command-line snippets.</li>\r\n<li>Jump to any section that is relevant to the task you are trying to complete.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"callout info\">\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The command substitution syntax, <code><mark>command</mark> $(<mark>command</mark>)</code>, used in the commands is available in many popular shells, such as <a href=\"https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/\" rel=\"ugc nofollow\">bash</a>, <a href=\"https://www.zsh.org/\" rel=\"ugc nofollow\">zsh</a>, and <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/\" rel=\"ugc nofollow\">Windows Powershell</a>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>If you want a 1-click way to deploy a Docker application to a live server, take a look at <a href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/products/app-platform\">DigitalOcean App Platform</a>.</p>\r\n<h2 id=\"purging-all-unused-or-dangling-images-containers-volumes-and-networks\"><a href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-remove-docker-images-containers-and-volumes#purging-all-unused-or-dangling-images-containers-volumes-and-networks\" onclick=\"navigator.clipboard.writeText(this.href);\">Purging All Unused or Dangling Images, Containers, Volumes, and Networks</a><a class=\"hash-anchor\" href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-remove-docker-images-containers-and-volumes#purging-all-unused-or-dangling-images-containers-volumes-and-networks\" aria-hidden=\"true\" onclick=\"navigator.clipboard.writeText(this.href);\"></a></h2>\r\n<p>Docker provides a single command that will clean up any resources &mdash; images, containers, volumes, and networks &mdash; that are <em>dangling</em> (not tagged or associated with a container):</p>', 1, '665f924972d67.png', '2024-06-04 22:15:44'),
